      "actions": [
        "Targeted retraining for The Beaumont \u2014 highest overtime ($25K), lowest publish rate (22%), and not effectively sharing open shifts. Specific overtime offenders (Violetta Jensen, Totelena, Aubrey) need manager coaching alongside the Veras workflow.",
        "Address low publish rates at Whisper Cove (25%), West Jordan (29%), and Ridgeview St. George (30%) \u2014 these are live communities with significant shift volumes. Schedule working sessions to identify why schedules aren't being published.",
        "Follow up on Cache Valley NPS score of 1 ('time off requests do not work') \u2014 investigate and resolve before it becomes a churn risk. Resurvey after fix.",
        "Investigate Sunridge Layton sending zero messages through the system (per QBR data) despite high publish rate \u2014 users may not be engaging with the messaging feature.",
        "Review the preferences feature requests backlog with product (5 open items dating to July 2025). SAL explicitly called out the suggested workers dropdown as confusing and wants preferences factored back in."
      ],
      "notes": "Large 14-community account, active onboarding. Strong momentum (messaging 4x growth, zero agency usage, overtime reductions at West Jordan and Ogden) mixed with significant problem communities \u2014 Beaumont in particular is dragging multiple metrics. NPS trending low at 2.8/5 with Cache Valley scoring 1. Cadence data unavailable from Circleback; Granola confirms QBR occurred.",
